nerated worker settings file and corresponding spawn arguments, while preserving existing hook isolation and legacy caller behavior.\n\n## Changes\n\n**Claude Worker Permission Bypass Fix**\n\n| Layer / File(s) | Summary |\n|---|---|\n| **Settings Contract & Documentation** <br> `src/backend/claude.ts` | `CLAUDE_WORKER_SETTINGS_BODY` extends from `{ disableAllHooks: true }` to include `permissions.defaultMode: 'bypassPermissions'` and `skipDangerousModePermissionPrompt: true`. Module documentation is rewritten to clarify worker permission posture and separation from hook isolation. |\n| **Worker Isolation Argv** <br> `src/backend/claude.ts` | `prepareWorkerIsolation()` appends `--permission-mode bypassPermissions` to worker spawn arguments, ensuring runtime permission configuration matches in-file settings. |\n| **Test Assertions** <br> `src/__tests__/claudeWorkerIsolation.test.ts` | Tests for `start()` and `resume()` verify `--permission-mode bypassPermissions` presence/order, forbid `--dangerously-skip-permissions`, and assert on-disk settings keys. Legacy caller test confirms no permission flags when `runId` is absent. User hook regression test validates full `CLAUDE_WORKER_SETTINGS_BODY` content. |\n| **Plan Documentation** <br> `plans/47-claude-workers-lose-bypass-permissions-under-generated-settings/*` | Plan index and detailed plan document the fix scope, implementation decisions (selected mode, placement in both settings and argv, dangerous-mode suppression), concrete tasks, and completed quality gates. |\n\n## Possibly Related PRs\n\n- [ralphkrauss/agent-orchestrator#45](https://github.com/ralphkrauss/agent-orchestrator/pull/45): Extends worker isolation by adding permission-mode settings and argv flags to the same `claude.ts` constants and corresponding test suite.\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 5</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (5 passe